The paper discusses empirical research in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and the assessment of hypotheses using statistical techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian inference, which is commonly used in machine learning and statistics, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses issues with p-value computation, which is a statistical technique used in hypothesis testing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
